#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.49"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.49:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.49:0.2"
msgid "5. Papātavagga"
msgstr "5. A Cliff"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 49. Paṭhamasinerupabbatarājasutta → sinerusuttaṃ (bj) | sineru 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.49:0.3"
msgid "49. Paṭhamasinerupabbatarājasutta"
msgstr "49. Sineru, King of Mountains (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.458"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.49:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sinerussa pabbatarājassa satta muggamattiyo "
"pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhipeyya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose a person was to place down on Sineru, the king of "
"mountains, seven pebbles the size of mung beans."

msgctxt "sn56.49:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

#. VAR: vā → yo ca (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: sinerupabbatarājā → sineru vā pabbatarājā (bj)
msgctxt "sn56.49:1.3"
msgid ""
"katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ—yā vā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā "
"upanikkhittā, yo vā sinerupabbatarājā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Which is more: the seven pebbles the size of mung beans? Or Sineru, the king "
"of mountains?”"

msgctxt "sn56.49:1.4"
msgid "“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ, yadidaṃ—sinerupabbatarājā;"
msgstr "“Sir, Sineru, the king of mountains, is certainly more."

msgctxt "sn56.49:1.5"
msgid "appamattikā satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā upanikkhittā."
msgstr "The seven pebbles the size of mung beans are tiny."

msgctxt "sn56.49:1.6"
msgid ""
"Saṅkhampi na upenti, upanidhampi na upenti, kalabhāgampi na upenti "
"sinerupabbatarājānaṃ upanidhāya satta muggamattiyo pāsāṇasakkharā "
"upanikkhittā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Compared to Sineru, they can’t be reckoned or compared, they’re not even a "
"fraction.”"

msgctxt "sn56.49:1.7"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa diṭṭhisampannassa puggalassa "
"abhisametāvino etadeva bahutaraṃ dukkhaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ; "
"appamattakaṃ avasiṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, for a person with comprehension, a noble disciple "
"accomplished in view, the suffering that’s over and done with is more, what’"
"s left is tiny."

msgctxt "sn56.49:1.8"
msgid ""
"Saṅkhampi na upeti, upanidhampi na upeti, kalabhāgampi na upeti, purimaṃ "
"dukkhakkhandhaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ upanidhāya yadidaṃ "
"sattakkhattuparamatā;"
msgstr ""
"Compared to the mass of suffering in the past that’s over and done with, it "
"can’t be reckoned or compared, it’s not even a fraction, since there are at "
"most seven more lives."

msgctxt "sn56.49:1.9"
msgid ""
"yo ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī "
"paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Such a person truly understands about suffering, its origin, its cessation, "
"and the path."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.49:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.49:2.2"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
